pragma circom 2.1.0;

// Proves the tenant knows the private payment data (paymentSecret, paymentNonce)
// that produces the public paymentCommitment for a given viewing request, per
// docs/zkproof/UrbanRentisha_TrustLayer_ZK_Proof_Documentation.md section 8/4.
//
// Compiled with `--prime bls12381` to match the deployed Soroban verifier's
// BLS12-381 pairing host functions (contracts/trust-verifier).
//
// Commitment construction: MiMCPermutation(paymentSecret, paymentNonce), a
// minimal one-way compression function using the x^5 S-box (gcd(5, r-1) = 1
// over the BLS12-381 scalar field r, so x -> x^5 is a bijection - the same
// S-box exponent Poseidon uses for this field), with a fixed `right` value
// injected into every round (Davies-Meyer-style, not a true Feistel network
// - there is no left/right swap each round, just a single accumulating
// state - "MiMCPermutation" is named accordingly, unlike circomlib's
// MiMCFeistel, which genuinely swaps halves).
//
// Round count: 220, matching circomlib's own documented security margin for
// an x^5 S-box MiMC construction over a similarly-sized field (their
// mimcsponge.circom: "log_5(field) ~= 110 => nRounds should be 220"). The
// algebraic degree of an n-round x^5 permutation is 5^n; for Groebner-basis
// / polynomial-interpolation attacks to be infeasible, that degree must
// exceed the field size (2^255 here). 5^220 vastly exceeds 2^255; an
// earlier 12-round version of this circuit did not (5^12 = 2^28, ~18x short
// of the field size) - that was a real algebraic-attack weakness, not a
// stylistic shortcut, caught and fixed before this revision.
//
// This replaces an earlier `secretSq + nonceSq == target` relation, which
// was NOT a binding commitment at all: that conic equation has on the
// order of r solutions over F_r, so any prover could choose an arbitrary
// secret and solve for a matching nonce via a modular square root, without
// ever knowing the real (secret, nonce) pair derived from the actual
// payment.
//
// Documented MVP limitation: this is NOT an independently audited
// Poseidon/MiMC parameter set. It is a minimal, self-contained
// construction sized to the same security margin circomlib documents for
// its own MiMC implementation. Production use should adopt a standard,
// audited primitive matched to this field.
